%20industry.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGary%20now%20makes%20less%20than%20he%20did%20working%20in%20Hollywood%20but%20says%20he's%20happier%20and%20wouldn't%20go%20back.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Gary%20Binkow%2C%20a%20former%20Hollywood%20producer%20who%20gave%20up%20his%20multimillion-dollar%20career%20to%20start%20a%20new%20business%20in%20the%20longevity%20industry.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20into%20the%20movie%20business%20because%20my%20one%20talent%20as%20a%20kid%20was%20that%20I%20was%20really%20good%20at%20watching%20TV%20and%20movies%20%E2%80%94%20I%20mean%2C%20I%20just%20inhaled%20everything%20I%20could.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20way%20my%20brain%20works%20is%20that%20I%20would%20watch%20TV%20shows%20and%20movies%20and%20try%20to%20unravel%20what%20it%20was%20about%20them%20that%20moved%20me%20and%20how%20the%20storytelling%20worked.%20And%20so%20then%2C%20when%20I%20found%20out%20you%20can%20go%20major%20in%20movie-making%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20do%20that.%20I%20went%20to%20Columbia%20University%20and%20majored%20in%20film%20because%2C%20frankly%2C%20I%20thought%20it%20would%20be%20easy.%20I'm%20always%20looking%20for%20the%20path%20of%20least%20resistance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20working%20for%20MTV%20in%20New%20York%20in%201980%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%2C%20after%20moving%20to%20California%2C%20worked%20my%20way%20up%20from%20an%20assistant%20working%20at%2020th%20Century%20Fox%20to%20a%20development%20executive%2C%20then%20eventually%20a%20producer%2C%20mainly%20based%20at%20Miramax%20Films.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20a%20long%20career%20in%20Hollywood.%20I%20made%20about%2030%20films%20on%20the%20independent%20side%20and%20had%20a%20successful%20run%20at%20Miramax.%20At%20the%20top%20of%20my%20career%2C%20I%20produced%20a%20movie%20called%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvey-weinstein-kenneth-cole-charity-deal-2017-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFinding%20Neverland%2C%20%3C%2Fa%3Ewhich%C2%A0came%20out%20in%202004%2C%C2%A0won%20a%20bunch%20of%20awards%2C%20and%20got%20nominated%20for%20several%20Oscars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20I%20had%20been%20successful%2C%20I%20still%20found%20my%20creative%20ideas%20blocked%20by%20industry%20gatekeepers%20like%20Harvey%20Weinstein%2C%20who%20repeatedly%20passed%20on%20them%20even%20though%20they'd%20made%20millions%20with%20other%20studios.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20decided%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20be%20in%20a%20system%20where%20I%20couldn't%20control%20my%20own%20destiny%20and%20realized%20I%20was%20really%20an%20entrepreneur.%20When%20you%20make%2030%20independent%20movies%2C%20you%20are%20essentially%20building%2030%20independent%20companies.%20So%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20use%20those%20skills%20to%20start%20my%20own%20company%20in%202005%2C%20Collective%20Digital%20Studios%2C%20a%20new%20media%20company%20offering%20services%20like%20content%20production%2C%20brand%20management%2C%20and%20distribution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEverybody%20in%20the%20movie%20business%20told%20me%20I%20was%20an%20idiot%20and%20crazy%20for%20leaving.%20But%20in%20the%20early%202000s%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0the%20early%20days%20of%20internet%20virality%20%E2%80%94%20we%20worked%20with%20content%20creators%20and%20comedians%20like%20Logan%20Paul%20and%20King%20Bach%20before%20they'd%20made%20it%20big%20and%20created%20a%20massive%20platform%20leveraging%20their%20expertise%20in%20hooking%20audiences%20with%20short%20video%20clips.%20As%20we%20expanded%2C%20we%20helped%20Katt%20Williams%20license%20his%20iconic%20comedy%20special%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Pimp%20Chronicles%2C%26quot%3B%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eto%20HBO%20in%202006%20and%20produced%20thousands%20of%20YouTube%20videos%2C%20driving%20strong%20profits%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0but%20something%20felt%20like%20it%20was%20missing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20decided%20I'd%20rather%20do%20something%20more%20powerful.%20I%20was%20good%20at%20helping%20people%20connect%20with%20audiences%20and%20telling%20better%20stories%2C%20but%20I%20wanted%20to%20do%20it%20with%20a%20purpose%20and%20a%20mission.%20So%20I%20left.%20In%202019%2C%20we%20sold%20the%20company%2C%20which%20is%20now%20known%20as%20Studio71%2C%20for%20a%20healthy%20exit%20to%20ProSieben%2C%20and%20I%20decided%20I%20wanted%20to%20use%20the%20same%20skill%20set%20in%20health%20and%20wellness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20my%20partner%20and%20I%20moved%20out%20of%20Los%20Angeles%20and%20onto%20an%20organic%20avocado%20farm%20in%20the%20beach%20town%20of%20Carpinteria%2C%20California.%20We've%20been%20working%20to%20rehabilitate%20it%2C%20and%20in%202020%2C%20I%20started%20The%20Swell%20Score%2C%20a%20membership-based%20online%20marketplace%20for%20holistic%20and%20clean%20supplements%20and%20other%20household%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20interested%20in%20holistic%20health%20for%20my%20whole%20life.%20I'm%20always%20looking%20for%20more%20natural%20ways%20to%20stay%20healthy%20and%20out%20of%20the%20sick%20care%20system.%20But%20there%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20misinformation%20and%20skepticism%20in%20the%20wellness%20space%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I%20understand%20that%20because%20I'm%20just%20as%20skeptical.%20So%2C%20at%20The%20Swell%20Score%2C%20we%20partner%20with%20medical%20experts%20to%20review%20wellness%20and%20beauty%20products%20and%20work%20with%20customers%20to%20teach%20them%20how%20to%20improve%20their%20health%20and%20live%20longer%2C%20happier%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Longevity%20Lab%2C%20which%20I%20opened%20in%20October%20in%20Carpinteria%2C%20is%20an%20expansion%20of%20that.%20It's%20a%20retail%20space%20where%20you%20can%20buy%20these%20products%20and%20see%20the%20difference%20for%20yourself.%20We%20offer%20everything%20from%20non-toxic%20mattresses%20and%20housewares%20to%20wellness%20supplements%2C%20beauty%20products%2C%20and%20bath%20items.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20the%20wellness%20space%20has%20been%20good%20to%20me%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0it's%20not%20nine%20figures%20good%20yet%2C%20but%20I%20have%20no%20interest%20in%20going%20back%20to%20Hollywood%3B%20the%20movie-making%20business%20is%20totally%20broken.%20I%20plan%20to%20keep%20building%20in%20this%20industry%2C%20and%20people%20have%20been%20really%20responsive.%20I%20think%20part%20of%20that%20is%20because%20I%20took%20some%20of%20the%20tactics%20of%20storytelling%20and%20brand%20building%20that%20I%20learned%20from%20the%20other%20company%20and%20applied%20them%20to%20health%20and%20wellness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20when%20I%20get%20asked%20to%20advise%20people%20and%20help%20them%20hone%20their%20business%20stories%20and%20strategies%2C%20the%20one%20thing%20I%20tell%20anybody%20who's%20getting%20started%20is%20that%20I%20would%20think%20of%20yourself%20as%20a%20media%20company%20first%2C%20not%20a%20product%20company.%20You%20know%2C%20with%20just%20one%20video%2C%20you%20could%20create%20your%20billion-dollar%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgary-binkow-producer-left-hollywood-pursue-second-career-longevity-wellness-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734958802000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6760892f8dee90d55ca0aaef%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgary-binkow-producer-left-hollywood-pursue-second-career-longevity-wellness-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Gary%20Binkow%20was%20an%20Emmy%20award-winning%20producer%20who%20is%20happier%20now%20that%20he's%20left%20his%20multimillion-dollar%20Hollywood%20career%20to%20start%20a%20longevity%20business.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ktangalakislippert%40businessinsider.com%20(Katherine%20Tangalakis-Lippert)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fga