%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFolks%20who%20are%20early%20in%20their%20career%20will%20often%20look%20at%20people%20who%20they%20think%20are%20successful%20and%20think%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%20be%20just%20like%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20sometimes%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-early-career-advice-2018-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eearly-career%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20a%20hard%20time%20distinguishing%20the%20reasons%20for%20a%20person's%20success%20from%20their%20bad%20habits.%20They%20might%20not%20know%20things%20that%20the%20company%20has%20been%20willing%20to%20work%20around%20or%20that%20hold%20that%20person%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20in%20my%20career%2C%20I%20over-indexed%20on%20emulating%20senior%20leaders.%20For%20example%2C%20I'd%20see%20some%20of%20them%20making%20sweeping%20statements%20like%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20future%2C%20or%2C%20this%20isn't%20the%20future.%26quot%3B%20They%20can%20get%20away%20with%20that%20because%20they've%20proven%20themselves%2C%20but%20I'd%20do%20the%20same%2C%20and%20it%20would%20fall%20on%20deaf%20ears.%20I%20hadn't%20yet%20earned%20that%20level%20of%20credibility%20and%20still%20needed%20to%20%26quot%3Bshow%20my%20work%26quot%3B%20before%20I%20earned%20that%20trust.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboss-management-leadership-advice-hiring-developing-people-earning-respect-2020-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esenior%20leader%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20Deel%2C%20I'm%20very%20conscious%20about%20how%20I%20present%20myself%20to%20early%20career%20folks.%20In%20larger%20meetings%2C%20I%20remind%20myself%20that%20there%20will%20be%20people%20on%20the%20call%20who%20view%20my%20role%20through%20a%20limited%20set%20of%20interactions.%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20pass%20on%20any%20bad%20behavior%20or%20shortcomings%20for%20them%20to%20emulate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20career%20story%20you%20want%20to