l%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bangladeshi%20Traders%20%26quot%3BForced%26quot%3B%20To%20Import%20From%20Pakistan%20Amid%20Growing%20Ties%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20concern%20for%20India%2C%20trade%20and%20maritime%20ties%20between%20Pakistan%20and%20Bangladesh%20seem%20to%20be%20getting%20stronger%2C%20with%20a%20second%20cargo%20vessel%20from%20Karachi%20reaching%20the%20Chittagong%20port%20this%20week.%20The%20Panama-flagged%20ship%20'MV%20Yuan%20Xiang%20Fa%20Zhan'%20entered%20Bangladeshi%20waters%20on%20Sunday%20afternoon%2C%20according%20to%20Bangladeshi%20media%20reports.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20vessel%2C%20which%20travelled%20via%20Karachi%2C%20Pakistan%2C%20and%20Dubai%2C%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%2C%20is%20carrying%20a%20substantial%20load%20of%20811%20containers%20of%20essential%20industrial%20materials%20such%20as%20soda%20ash%2C%20dolomite%2C%20and%20marble%20blocks%2C%20along%20with%20goods%20like%20garments%20raw%20materials%2C%20sugar%2C%20and%20electronic%20products%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20Follow%2C%20No%20Index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dhakatribune.com%2Fbangladesh%2F368729%2Fpakistani-ship-brings-goods-to-bangladesh-for-the%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDhaka%20Tribune%20%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20Follow%2C%20No%20Index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.observerbd.com%2Fnews%2F504034%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDaily%20Observer%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20development%20came%20a%20day%20after%20Bangladesh's%20interim%20leader%2C%20Professor%20Muhammad%20Yunus%2C%20met%20Pakistan's%20Prime%20Minister%20Shehbaz%20Sharif%20in%20Egypt's%20Cairo%2C%20where%20Dhaka%20and%20Islamabad%20%26quot%3Bagreed%20to%20strengthen%20relations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EConcern%20For%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQuoting%20sources%2C%20The%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20Follow%2C%20No%20Index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Finternational%2Fworld-news%2Fsecond-cargo-ship-from-pakistan-reaches-bangladesh-in-as-many-months%2Farticleshow%2F116574544.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20that%20traders%20in%20Bangladesh%20are%20being%20forced%20to%20import%20goods%20from%20Pakistan.%20It%20also%20said%20that%20some%20officials%20in%20Bangladesh's%20shipping%20ministry%20are%20suggesting%20to%20review%20of%20the%20India-Bangladesh%20shipping%20pact%2C%20which%20gave%20India%20access%20to%20Chittagong%20and%20Mongla%20ports.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChittagong%20Port%20is%20a%20strategically%20located%20docking%20site%20in%20the%20Bay%20of%20Bengal.%20Over%20the%20years%2C%20India%20has%20used%20its%20relationship%20with%20ousted%20premier%20Sheikh%20Hasina%20to%20keep%20an%20eye%20on%20the%20activities%20at%20Chittagong%20port%2C%20where%20in%202004%2C%20around%201%2C500%20boxes%20of%20Chinese%20ammunition%20were%20confiscated.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20consignment%2C%20worth%20an%20estimated%20USD%204.5-7%20million%2C%20was%20allegedly%20masterminded%20by%20Pakistan's%20intelligence%20agency%2C%20the%20Inter-Services%20Intelligence%20(ISI).%20The%20consignment%20was%20allegedly%20meant%20to%20be%20delivered%20to%20banned%20terrorist%20outfit%20ULFA%20(United%20Liberation%20Front%20of%20Asom)%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENew%20Delhi%20worries%20a%20resurgence%20of%20Islamist%20extremism%20in%20Bangladesh%20could%20target%20India%20and%20support%20insurgent%20groups%20in%20northeastern%20states.%20Adding%20to%20India's%20worries%2C%20Bangladesh%2C%20in%20September%2C%20removed%20the%20clause%20which%20required%20the%20port%20authorities%20to%20physically%20inspect%20cargo%20from%20Pakistan%20on%20arrival.%20This%20makes%20it%20easier%20for%20Pakistani%20vessels%20to%20use%20the%20maritime%20routes%20without%20the%20physical%20inspection%20of%20cargo.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20the%20restrictive%20trade%20policy%20under%20Ms%20Hasina%20required%20cargo%20from%20Pakistan%20to%20be%20offloaded%20in%20Malaysia%2C%20Singapore%2C%20or%20Sri%20Lanka%20and%20then%20transferred%20to%20other%20vessels%20that%20carried%20them%20to%20Bangladesh.%20Indian%20officials%20kept%20a%20watchful%20eye%20on%20sea%20routes%20that%20connect%20Chittagong.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EBangladesh-Pakistan%20Ties%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuhammad%20Yunus%2C%20the%2084-year-old%20Nobel%20laureate%2C%20who%20took%20over%20as%20leader%20of%20Bangladesh's%20interim%20administration%20in%20August%2C%20is%20a%20staunch%20opponent%20of%20Ms%20Hasina's%20policies%2C%20which%20were%20fundamentally%20pro-India%20and%20anti-Pakistan.%20Since%20he%20came%20to%20power%2C%20one%20of%20his%20areas%20of%20focus%20has%20been%20improving%20relations%20with%20Islamabad.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20major%20development%20in%20this%20regard%20was%20to%20initiate%20direct%20maritime%20connectivity%20between%20the%20two%20previously%20hostile%20Muslim-majority%20nations%2C%20which%20were%20once%20one%20country.%20In%20November%2C%20Chinese%20cargo%20ship%20'MV%20Yuan%20Xian%20Fa%20Zhong'%20from%20Karachi%2C%20arrived%20in%20Chittagong%2C%20marking%20the%20first-ever%20direct%20maritime%20contact%20between%20the%20two%20countries%20in%20over%20five%20decades--%20since%20Bangladesh%20was%20formed%20in%201971.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Yunus%20has%20also%20met%20the%20Pakistani%20Prime%20Minister%20twice%20since%20August.%20The%20latest%20meeting%20was%20in%20Egypt's%20Cairo%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20D-8%20summit.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20statement%20from%20the%20office%20of%20the%20Chief%20Adviser%2C%20Mr%20Yunus%20stressed%20the%20importance%20of%20resolving%20the%20longstanding%20issues%20stemming%20from%20Dhaka's%201971%20bloody%20separation%20from%20Islamabad.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Sharif%20called%20Bangladesh%20a%20%26quot%3Bbrotherly%20country%26quot%3B%20and%20expressed%20optimism%20on%20enhancing%20Islamabad%20and%20Dhaka%20ties%20and%20stressed%20the%20need%20for%20a%20strategic%20partnership.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20leaders%20also%20%26quot%3Bagreed%20to%20strengthen%20relations%20between%20the%20two%20countries%20through%20increased%20trade%2C%20commerce%2C%20and%20exchange%20of%20sports%20and%20cultural%20delegations%26quot%3B%2C%20as%20per%20the%20statement%20from%20Yunus'%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734949680000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Fir03hnug_mv-yuan-jian-fa-zhong-twitter_625x300_23_December_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdhaka-islamabad-maritime-ties-bangladeshi-traders-forced-to-import-from-pakistan-as-2nd-ship-from-karachi-docks-in-chittagong-7313320%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20a%20concern%20for%20India%2C%20trade%20and%20maritime%20ties%20between%20Pakistan%20and%20Bangladesh%20seem%20to%20be%20getting%20stronger%2C%20with%20a%20second%20cargo%20vessel%20from%20Karachi%20reaching%20the%20Chittagong%20port%20this%20week.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdhaka-islamabad-maritime-ties-bangladeshi-traders-forced-to-import-from-pakistan-as-2nd-ship-from-karachi-docks-in-chittagong-7313320%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ranveer-Aditya%20Dhar%E2%80%99s%20action%20thriller%20title%20REVEALED%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734949630000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-116598544%2Cimgsize-727260.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Franveer-singh-and-aditya-dhars-upcoming-action-thriller-title-revealed-details-inside%2Farticleshow%2F116598549.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20