0set%20alight%20on%20a%20Brooklyn%20train%20by%20a%20man%20she%20was%20not%20thought%20to%20know.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1516%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fclygk48nxgzo%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fclygk48nxgzo.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fclygk48nxgzo.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kolkata%20Man%20Gets%20Divorce%20As%20%26quot%3BImposition%20Of%20Wife's%20Friend%26quot%3B%20Is%20Deemed%20Cruelty%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Calcutta%20High%20Court%20has%20granted%20a%20divorce%20decree%20to%20a%20husband%20on%20the%20grounds%20of%20cruelty%2C%20which%20includes%20%26quot%3Bimposition%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20wife's%20friend%20and%20family%20on%20him%20and%20lodging%20of%20a%20false%20case%20of%20matrimonial%20cruelty%20by%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20division%20bench%20presided%20by%20Justice%20Sabyasachi%20Bhattacharyya%20set%20aside%20the%20judgment%20of%20the%20trial%20court%20that%20refused%20a%20divorce%20decree%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20husband%2C%20terming%20it%20as%20perverse%20and%20erroneous.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20in%20its%20judgment%20delivered%20on%20December%2019%20that%20a%20sufficiently%20strong%20case%20of%20mental%20cruelty%20has%20been%20made%20out%20by%20the%20appellant%20(husband)%20against%20the%20respondent%20(wife)%20to%20justify%20the%20grant%20of%20divorce%20on%20such%20grounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%2C%20also%20comprising%20Justice%20Uday%20Kumar%2C%20granted%20the%20divorce%20decree%20to%20the%20husband%20on%20the%20grounds%20of%20cruelty%2C%20thereby%20severing%20the%20marriage%20between%20the%20two.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20noted%20that%20the%20continued%20presence%20of%20the%20woman%20friend%20and%20others%20of%20the%20wife's%20family%20at%20the%20official%20residential%20quarters%20of%20the%20husband%20at%20Kolaghat%20in%20East%20Midnapore%20district%20despite%20his%20objection%20and%20discomfort%20on%20such%20count%20is%20borne%20out%20by%20the%20records.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSuch%20imposition%20of%20friend%20and%20family%20of%20the%20respondent%20on%20the%20husband%20at%20his%20quarter%20against%20his%20will%2C%20sometimes%20even%20when%20the%20respondent-wife%20herself%20was%20not%20there%2C%20over%20a%20continuous%20period%20of%20time%2C%20can%20definitely%20be%20constituted%20as%20cruelty%2C%20since%20it%20might%20very%20well%20have%20made%20life%20impossible%20for%20the%20appellant%2C%20which%20would%20come%20within%20the%20broader%20purview%20of%20cruelty%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20observed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20the%20wife%2C%20in%20the%20present%20case%2C%20unilaterally%20took%20a%20decision%20of%20refusal%20to%20have%20conjugal%20life%20with%20the%20husband%20for%20a%20considerable%20period%2C%20and%20there%20is%20admittedly%20a%20long%20period%20of%20continuous%20separation%2C%20unerringly%20indicating%20that%20the%20matrimonial%20bond%20has%20gone%20beyond%20repair.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20counsel%20for%20the%20husband%20submitted%20that%20the%20wife%20used%20to%20devote%20most%20of%20her%20family%20time%20with%20the%20woman%20friend%2C%20claiming%20that%20itself%20constitutes%20an%20act%20of%20cruelty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20couple%20had%20got%20married%20on%20December%2015%2C%202005.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20husband%20had%20on%20September%2025%2C%202008%2C%20instituted%20the%20divorce%20suit%20and%20on%20October%2027%20the%20same%20year%2C%20the%20wife%20sent%20a%20complaint%20against%20the%20husband%20and%20his%20family%20by%20registered%20post%20to%20the%20Nabadwip%20police%20station%2C%20within%20whose%20jurisdictional%20limits%20the%20husband's%20paternal%20residence%20was%20situated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20criminal%20proceeding%20was%20accordingly%20initiated%20under%20Section%20498A%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC)%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20complaint.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20lawyer%20produced%20before%20the%20bench%20the%20criminal%20court's%20judgment%20whereby%20the%20husband%20and%20his%20family%20members%20had%20been%20acquitted%20of%20the%20charges%20brought%20against%20them%20by%20the%20wife%2C%20contending%20that%20such%20acquittal%20and%20the%20timing%20of%20the%20complaint%20go%20on%20to%20show%20that%20it%20was%20entirely%20false.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20argued%20that%20such%20baseless%20harassment%20also%20constitutes%20cruelty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20wife's%20lawyer%20submitted%20that%20the%20husband%20had%20failed%20to%20prove%20his%20case%20of%20cruelty%2C%20and%20as%20such%20the%20divorce%20suit%20was%20rightly%20dismissed%20by%20the%20trial%20court%20judge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENoting%20that%20the%20wife%20resided%20at%20her%20official%20quarters%20at%20Narkeldanga%20in%20Kolkata%20from%20May%202008%2C%20while%20the%20husband%20stayed%20at%20Kolaghat%20in%20East%20Midnapore%20district%2C%20the%20court%20said%20the%20deliberate%20intention%20of%20the%20wife%20not%20to%20return%20to%20conjugal%20life%20itself%20constitutes%20cruelty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20division%20bench%20said%20since%20there%20was%20no%20contemporaneous%20complaint%20by%20the%20wife%20throughout%20the%20marriage%20and%20rather%2C%20she%20lived%20with%20the%20husband%20for%20three%20years%20from%202005%20to%202008%20without%20any%20grievance%20being%20raised%2C%20coupled%20with%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20wife's%20mother%20and%20her%20friend%20lived%20in%20the%20Kolaghat%20quarters%20even%20when%20the%20wife%20was%20not%20there%2C%20indicate%20the%20allegations%20subsequently%20levelled%20against%20the%20husband%20were%20mere%20afterthought.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20quite%20evident%20that%20the%20bald%20allegations%20made%20in%20the%20complaint%20by%20the%20wife%20under%20Section%20498A%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%20without%20any%20particulars%2C%20